Headlines.Headline: Arca Biopharma Receives Patent For Heart-Failure Treatment
Headlines.Author: Nathan Becker

#text: DOW JONES NEWSWIRES Arca Biopharma Inc.

said it has received a patent for its methods of treating heart-failure patients with beta blocker bucindolol based on genetic testing, which could give the company 15 years of drug exclusivity. Shares soared 13% to $3.00 premarket. As of Thursday's close, the stock had dropped 35% in the past year. Arca President and Chief Executive Michael Bristow said the patent will extend the company's intellectual-property protection around bucindolol and, if approved for marketing, will give its Gencaro drug market exclusivity into 2025.

Headlines.BodyHeadline: Arca Biopharma Receives Patent For Heart-Failure Treatment

Headlines.Headline: BEFORE THE BELL: US Stock Futures Fall Before Data
Headlines.Author: Steve Goldstein

PARAGRAPH.#text: By Steve Goldstein U.S. stock futures edged lower Thursday heading into the extended weekend with attention turning to the payrolls report for clues on whether the economy can continue to mend. S&P 500 futures fell 5 points to 914.20 and Nasdaq 100 futures dropped 5.75 points to 1,473. Futures on the Dow Jones Industrial Average fell 38 points to 8,410. Data on manufacturing and housing as well as upbeat General Mills results helped U.S. stocks rise on Wednesday, with the Dow Jones Industrial Average rising 57 points, the Nasdaq Composite rising 10 points and the S&P 500 adding 4 points.

Headlines.BodyHeadline: BEFORE THE BELL: US Stock Futures Fall Before Data
